<emphasis id="018BFD68400A5F21FF50FBB44E5E3C31" box="[162,314,1086,1107]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="296">boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group species. In the adult the main differences are in the face with a vague central vitta, which is also present in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400A5F21FE05FBF14DC83CF2" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[503,684,1147,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400A5F21FE05FBF14DC83CF2" box="[503,684,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="296">C. boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Other 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400A5F21FF50FB104E5E3CCD" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[162,314,1178,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400A5F21FF50FB104E5E3CCD" box="[162,314,1178,1199]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="296">boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group species have a clear and distinct black vitta. 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400A5F21FED8FB334EDA3CAC" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[298,446,1209,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mamorum">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400A5F21FED8FB334EDA3CAC" box="[298,446,1209,1230]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="296">C. mamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400A5F21FDA6FB334C6E3CAF" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[596,778,1208,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400A5F21FDA6FB334C6E3CAF" box="[596,778,1208,1230]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="296">C. boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having yellow, not black, hairs on the face, vittae on the mesonotum, and tergites 3 and 4 with a band of yellow hairs anteriorly. The puparium can be distinguished by features of the posterior breathing tube that is punctate above the transverse ridge, and is only as wide as the width of a pupal spiracle. The posterior breathing tube is also punctate in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400A5F21FF50FA244E3C3DA1" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[162,344,1454,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400A5F21FF50FA244E3C3DA1" box="[162,344,1454,1475]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="296">C. boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in that species it is wider than the pupal spiracles. The posterior breathing tube is also long in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400A5F21FEC3FA614EA03E63" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[305,452,1515,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mamorum">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400A5F21FEC3FA614EA03E63" box="[305,452,1515,1537]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="296">C. mamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being more than the width of the puparium. In 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400A5F21FE78F9804D5B3E7D" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[394,575,1546,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boqueronense">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400A5F21FE78F9804D5B3E7D" box="[394,575,1546,1567]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="296">C. boqueronense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is shorter than the width of the puparium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A400A5F21FF50F9DC4E9F3EE9" blockId="29.[162,778,1622,1675]" pageId="29" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="018BFD68400A5F21FF50F9DC4F993E09" box="[162,253,1622,1643]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="296">Biology:</emphasis>
Reared from larvae found in a fallen, decaying bromeliad (
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9400A5F21FEA3F9FF4E943EE9" box="[337,496,1653,1675]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="29" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bromeliaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
